dct_title_s: Plan de Lhasa / from a survey of C.H.D. Ryder R. E., D. S. O.  and Captn. H.M. Cowie R.E., 1904.
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by line forms. Marshy fields and dry canal are shown. "The Ling Kor (pilgrim road) [Lingkhor Kora] is shewn by a black line length 5 miles." Also locates Linga = Summer residence with garden and Gompa = Monastery. Includes an index: Reference [to locations]. From "The Geographical Journal." vol. 26. no. 4.A copy of this volume is available from RECAP. Call number: G7 .J6874 vol 26, July to December 1905. A printed copy of this map is in volume.
